article.headline: Coastal Carolina 81, McNeese State 67
article.story: CONWAY, S.C. (AP) -- Moses Sonko had 24 points and 13 rebounds to lead Coastal Carolina to an 81-67 win over McNeese State on Tuesday night. The Chanticleers (6-6) never trailed, but didn't put the Cowboys (5-9) away until late in the second half. Coastal Carolina's lead was 58-56 when Steven Sexton's free throws with 8:02 to go started an 18-6 run over the next seven minutes. The final margin of 14 points matched the Chanticleers biggest lead of the game. Coastal Carolina forced 21 turnovers and only gave away the ball eight times to make up for being outrebounded 40-25 by McNeese State. Troy Aaron scored 19 points and had five assists, Jarvis Bradley had 11 points and seven rebounds and Quentin Gonzales scored six points and pulled down 10 rebounds for the Cowboys. Jack Leasure also scored 24 points for Coastal Carolina.
